originalText.text: This place is okay considering it is a New York City facility. If you are able to get there when it is not so crowded it is at least bearable. The problem is that the HRA is giving inaccurate information by saying that no SNAP cases will be closed in the months of December of 2021 and January and February of 2022  because that is not true. They also do not tell you that mailing in your recertification or faxing your recertification will not work and the only way to recertify is by a telephone call when they call you. The problem with that is there are so many scam and fake calls that you never know if the call you're receiving is a legitimate call that you should answer. If you don't answer because you think it's a scam call then your case will be closed and you have to reapply all over again. This system needs to be fixed to prevent people from losing their benefits needlessly and having to go through the process all over again. This only makes additional work for the workers and much frustration for the recipients. It is a prime example of a bungling bureaucracy which needs improvement.
